What you need to know:

A notice from the Immigration Department said all foreigners previously allowed to stay in the country despite expiry of their visas must now leave or apply for residence permits in a fortnight.When the country issued an amnesty in April, it allowed foreigners to continue staying without paying an extra coin for visa renewals.That law proposes penalties of up to three years in jail or up to Sh500,000 fine for those found in the country illegally. It also allows those with expired documents to be declared prohibited immigrants and deported.Â 